One third of amphibians are at risk of extinction, with 1,856 species under threat due to habitat loss, climate change, and pollution.
Efforts to protect amphibians are crucial, as hundreds more species could vanish in the coming years.
The decline in frog populations is alarming, with some species already extinct.
Urbanization and agricultural development have led to a loss of habitat for salamanders.
Scientists are concerned about the rapid rate of extinction among amphibians, with over 3,000 species facing imminent threats.
Conservation efforts are needed to prevent further losses in amphibian populations.
